    "whatItDoes": "Diagnoses and fixes Postgres query patterns that cause excessive data transfer from a database to an application. Works by analyzing pg_stat_statements output to find queries returning too many rows, too many columns, or running too frequently. Covers SELECT * abuse, missing pagination, JOIN duplication, and application-side aggregation.",
